With a working proof of concept, I was able to demonstrate that producing a podcast was a viable and achievable goal. 
At the time, however, the team underestimated the level of ongoing dedication a podcast requires. 
The idea immediately captured their attention, but the reality of execution took time to set in — and eventually, they gained a clear understanding of what the commitment truly involved.

Led the launch of "The Hive" podcast studio from concept to completion. 
Conducted equipment research, coordinated with team members on the physical build-out, and oversaw the full technical setup. 
The finished space was completed within one year and is now capable of hosting both podcast recordings and live streams at a professional level.
